@node About "What is Coder?"

	@{u}About Coder.@{uu}

Coder is a small CLI utility that enables you to encrypt files.
On the first pass of a file it will encrypt the contents and on the second it will decrypt it.

The resultant encrypted file will be slighlty bigger than the original (somewhere around 12 bytes).

Coder can automatically detect whether a file has been previously encrypted by it. It will perfrom either encryption or decryption depending on this state.

The program was compiled with "Standard maths" so it will work on all systems.

